<div id="review_17692536" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/17692536" />
    <a title="Jaime" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/159833-jaime"><img alt="Jaime" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1611350268p2/159833.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/17692536?book_show_action=true">Mar 13, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jaime" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jaime" href="/user/show/159833-jaime">Jaime</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/159833-jaime?shelf=read-2005">read-2005</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/159833-jaime?shelf=historical-1800s">historical-1800s</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer17692536" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1596449547417998947">Actually, I didn’t quite finish this book. But I invested so much time in it, I’m counting it, dammit. I was disappointed in it — I was looking for much more story about the people, and much less descriptions of battles. I expected it to be a story about Duncan, Maggie, and Jacob. And since Maggie was essentially the narrator, I was disappointed that there were large stretches where you just didn’t read anything about her. What it comes down to is that I just lost interest in the story.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


